The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, Feb. 2 (PTI): The Centre is planning to make it mandatory for the marital status of women to be stamped on their passports to ensure that NRI husbands who desert their wives are taken to task under Indian laws.

 The Centre is also planning to ask the US and the UK, the two countries with the largest population of NRIs, to specify the marital status on the visa. The proposals will soon be taken up with the foreign ministry, an official said.

 New Delhi (PTI): The Delhi police constable, who tried to enter the high-security residence of Prime Minister Manmohan Singh in a drunken state on Thursday, has been suspended but no case has been filed against Bhurra Singh. 

 New Delhi (PTI): Veteran Marxist leader Harkishan Singh Surjeet was hospitalised on Friday following a urinary infection. The condition of the 91-year-old former CPM general secretary was serious but stable, party sources said. 

 Shimla (PTI): People of Himachal Pradeshs Kinnaur district popularly known as Kinners are up in arms against Madhur Bhandarkars latest film Traffic Signal which uses the name of the community to refer to eunuchs and threatened legal action.

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has told local civic bodies that they would face contempt charges if they did not comply with its order on maintenance of public toilets in the city. 

 Mumbai (PTI): Actor and cinematographer Vijay Arora, famed for his performance in Yaadon Ki Baraat, died on Friday. He was 62.




